<HEADLINE>
<P>
OUTTAKES: 'HOUSE' WARMING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Pat H. Broeske 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Russia House" won't be released until the Christmas season, but already the 
movie's promotional push is underway, through a campaign for the just-published 
paperback edition of John le Carre's best-seller. 
</P>
<P>
Promo and art -- of stars Sean Connery and Michelle Pfeiffer -- can be found 
inside the front cover of 2 million Bantam reprints. 
</P>
<P>
The same plug appears in a dozen other newly reissued Le Carre titles from 
Bantam. A recent 30-second national TV spot pushed both book and film; ditto 
trailers in theaters. When Bantam issues the "movie edition" of "Russia House" 
in November, the movie's art will grace the cover. 
</P>
<P>
 When MGM/UA's promotion is in full swing, promises Greg Morrison, marketing 
president for producing Pathe Entertainment, "it will be hard to miss us." Pat 
H. Broeske 
</P>
</TEXT>
