<HEADLINE>
<P>
MIXED MEDIA; 
</P>
<P>
*** 1/2 "THE VALUE OF IGNORANCE" SINEAD O'CONNOR, POLYGRAM MUSIC VIDEO 
($19.95): ITEMS IN THIS PERIODIC SURVEY OF POP-RELATED BOOKS, VIDEOCASSETTES 
AND LASER DISCS ARE RATED ON A SCALE OF ONE STAR (POOR) TO FIVE (A CLASSIC). 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS WILLMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
O'Connor and director John Maybury avoid the most obvious -- and ignorant -- 
approaches to filming music in this 35-minute video of a 1988 London concert. 
</P>
<P>
Nearly all camera angles are close-ups of her famous profile; though a backing 
band and crowd noise are heard, one fleeting look at the drummer is the only 
non-O'Connor shot. Sound static? Hardly. All sorts of colorful, abstract visual 
overlays add to and play with the black-and-white footage, somehow never 
distracting from the intimate tone the Irish singer strikes on stage; it 
remains baldly emotional. Johnny-come-lately fans take note: Seven of the eight 
songs come from her first album, not its current successor. CHRIS WILLMAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
