RECORD RACK: ** THE ALLMAN BROTHERS BAND, "SEVEN TURNS," EPIC.: ALBUMS ARE 
RATED ON A SCALE OF ONE STAR (POOR) TO FIVE (A CLASSIC). 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE BOEHM 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two decades, two funerals and far more than seven twists and turns in the road 
separate the Allman Brothers from their peak. 
</P>
<P>
Yet two lingering qualities from the old days allow them to continue with 
dignity intact and rehash avoided. Those are Gregg Allman's way with a soulful 
blues vocal, and guitarist Dickey Betts' ability to shape an instrumental 
excursion into a work of dramatic architecture. Not a brilliant album, but one 
that's solid and welcome. MIKE BOEHM 
</P>
