<P>
BOOK TELLS HOW TO GAIN FROM MOVES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Moving Buildings for Profit" is the title of a new self-teaching investment 
manual written by Jim Dunham, president of the American Architectural 
Preservation Group Inc. 
</P>
<P>
In the 200-page manual Dunham explains how to find lots, how to evaluate the 
moving contractor, get free buildings, arrange financing and walk through the 
processing procedure. Included are checklists, forms and examples of documents 
used in the relocation process. 
</P>
<P>
The manual is available by writing The House Relocator, 2600 S. Hoover St., Los 
Angeles, Calif. 90007. Cost is $85, tax and shipping included. 
