<HEADLINE>
<P>
GRAND OPENINGS: TOWNHOUSES IN IRVINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Corte Bella, one of the last residential neighborhoods to be developed in 
Irvine's Westpark community, opens today with 260 condominiums and townhouses. 
</P>
<P>
Developed by Newport Beach-based RGC -- formerly Recreations Group of Cos. -- 
Corte Bella was designed by the architectural firm of McLarand, Vasquez &amp; 
Partners Inc. in a "Euro-Villa" courtyard concept that minimizes the presence 
of cars. 
</P>
<P>
The 35 two- and three-bedroom units in the first phase range in size from 1,075 
to 2,185 square feet and are priced from $175,000 to $302,000. The monthly 
association fee is $125, and move-ins are scheduled to begin in December or 
early January. 
</P>
<P>
The sales office is open from 10 a.m. to 5 p.m. daily at 15 Venezia Aisle near 
Harvard Avenue and San Leon Road, reached from the Culver Drive exit of the San 
Diego (405) Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Homes in Escondido 
</P>
<P>
Montclair, the third and largest of three communities in Lomas del Lago 
Estates, opens today in Escondido with 248 single-family houses. 
</P>
<P>
The 20 three-, four- and five-bedroom houses in the first phase are offered in 
five one- and two-story plans ranging in size from 2,543 to 3,500 square feet. 
Prices range from $335,000 to $480,000. 
</P>
<P>
Features include three- and four-car garages, lots averaging more than 13,000 
square feet and kitchens with center food islands and breakfast nooks. The 
153-acre Lomas del Lago Estates development overlooks Escondido's planned 
18-hole municipal golf course. 
</P>
<P>
Move-ins are scheduled to begin late this year, according to a spokeswoman for 
the developers, a joint venture of Lomas Group, Lomas Santa Fe Inc. and 
Tech-Built Inc. 
</P>
<P>
The monthly association fee of $121.75 covers upkeep of the community's tennis 
and swim club. The sales office and furnished models are open daily from 10 
a.m. to 5 p.m. near West Frontage Road, reached from the westbound Via Rancho 
Parkway exit of the Escondido (15) Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Moreno Valley Ranch 
</P>
<P>
Spyglass Hill at Moreno Valley Ranch opens today in a Moreno Valley development 
that features a 27-hole golf course. 
</P>
<P>
The 29 houses in the first phase of the 55-home project by Lewis Homes of 
California have three and four bedrooms and range from 2,778 to 3,049 square 
feet. Prices in the first phase range from $288,990 to $415,990 and move-ins 
are scheduled to begin in November. 
</P>
<P>
Three furnished models are open from 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. daily at 28354 
Championship Drive, reached from the southbound Moreno Beach Drive exit of the 
Pomona (60) Freeway. 
</P>
