<HEADLINE>
<P>
SINGLE TRAVELER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Now I know: Single people do get cheated when it comes to room distribution on 
a tour. 
</P>
<P>
We pay extra but come up with less. On a recent tour, nearly every night my 
room faced rear buildings so close that I had to keep blinds closed. Roofs 
and/or balconies were so close that I locked my windows and doors and spent the 
night in an airless room. 
</P>
<P>
Complaining to the tour guide and desk was of no use. Several times I looked at 
couples' rooms to see a view of lake or mountains. I wish tour companies and 
hotels would consider single travelers, especially women, as people, too. 
</P>
<P>
FRANCES BLAKE 
</P>
<P>
Lemoore, Calif. 
</P>
</TEXT>
