LANSING, Mich. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lt. Gov. Martha Griffiths, who served in Congress for 20 years and was a force 
behind passage of the equal rights amendment, has been dropped from the 1990 
ticket by Gov. James J. Blanchard. 
</P>
<P>
Blanchard praised Griffiths, 78, as "the premier stateswoman," but said Friday 
he asked her to step aside because he no longer considers her ready to assume 
the governor's post at a moment's notice. 
</P>
