<HEADLINE>
<P>
FREEWAY DEATHS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Whoa! Just a minute. Since when is it Caltrans' responsibility to protect 
lawbreakers ("Mother Learns Her Boy Died Crossing I-5," Aug. 17)? 
</P>
<P>
It is a damn shame there have been so many killed while trying to bolt across 
the freeways in their attempt to avoid the checkpoints. But let's put the blame 
where it belongs, and it is not Caltrans. 
</P>
<P>
It is squarely on the people who are doing the running, and in this case the 
fault of the mother (sorry to say) who took six kids and tried to run across 
eight lanes of highway. Please don't try to tell me she did not know it was 
dangerous. 
</P>
<P>
DON MORRISON 
</P>
<P>
Ramona 
</P>
