<HEADLINE>
<P>
LITTLE LEAGUE WORLD SERIES; 
</P>
<P>
PENNSYLVANIANS OUST CYPRESS, 5-4 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WILLIAMSPORT, Pa. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bobby Shannon's two-run homer in the fifth inning lifted Shippensburg, Pa., to 
a 5-4 victory over Cypress on Saturday, sending the Pennsylvania team into the 
championship game of the Little League World Series against Taiwan. 
</P>
<P>
To clinch the victory, Shippensburg thwarted a no-out squeeze bunt in the 
bottom of the sixth and final inning. 
</P>
<P>
Pinch-hitter Joe Katchka bunted with Eddie Zamora at third, Katchka was out at 
first and Zamora was tagged out as he dove for the plate. 
</P>
<P>
Pitcher David Orndorff struck out eight and drove in two runs for Shippensburg. 
</P>
<P>
In the fifth, Orndorff beat out a two-hopper to shortstop, scoring Jimmy Smith 
to tie the score. Shannon hit the next pitch over the left-field fence to make 
it 5-3. 
</P>
<P>
Kerrie Cordero homered in the fifth for Cypress, which had a 3-0 lead after two 
innings. 
</P>
<P>
Shippensburg will play Taiwan today. Taiwan advanced by defeating Trail 
(Canada), 20-1. 
</P>
<P>
The first-inning run snapped Taiwan's nine-game scoreless streak. 
</P>
<P>
Taiwan had sent 16 teams to Williamsport previously. Thirteen won titles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
