<TEXT>
<P>
Ernie Irvan took the lead on lap 410 and held off Rusty Wallace by a car length 
for his first career Winston Cup victory in the Busch 500 at Bristol 
International Raceway in Bristol, Tenn. 
</P>
<P>
Irvan went in front when Dale Earnhardt tried to get past a lapped car. 
</P>
<P>
Irvan led the rest of the way to win $49,600 in the Morgan-McClure Racing 
Team's Chevrolet. 
</P>
<P>
Wallace continually tried to get past Irvan in the final laps, but held on to 
finished second. Winston Cups points leader Mark Martin was third; Terry 
Labonte was fourth; and Sterling Marlin finished fifth. 
</P>
<P>
Irvan averaged 91.782 m.p.h. on Bristol's steep, .533-mile oval in the only 
night race on the Winston Cup circuit. 
</P>
