<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: SANTA CLARITA MAN, 27, DROWNS AFTER SEIZURE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Santa Clarita man drowned Saturday afternoon after falling into a swimming 
pool at the condominium complex where he lived, sheriff's deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
Kevin Morris, 27, was standing beside the pool in the 24300 block of Venturi 
Drive when he suffered a seizure about 12:30 p.m. and fell in, said Lt. Don 
Rodriguez of the Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department. 
</P>
<P>
Morris was alone at the pool, Rodriguez said. 
</P>
<P>
Paramedics and sheriff's deputies arrived at the Lakeshore Condominiums pool 
and tried to revive Morris, Rodriguez said. 
</P>
<P>
Morris was taken to Henry Mayo Newhall Hospital, where he was pronounced dead. 
</P>
</TEXT>
