<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPY CHARGES UPHELD ON S. KOREA LAWMAKER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SEOUL, Korea 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
South Korea's supreme court rejected appeals by a dissident lawmaker Friday and 
upheld espionage charges against him and a 10-year prison sentence. 
</P>
<P>
The court ruled that Suh Kyung-won was guilty of espionage by leaking state 
secrets during his trip to communist North Korea. Suh had claimed that security 
officials forced him to make false confessions 
</P>
