<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fire investigators are looking for two boys who they suspect started a fire 
that destroyed one house and damaged two others Thursday in Paradise Hills. 
</P>
<P>
A home video taken by one of the residents shows two boys, about 9 or 10 years 
old, leaving the scene of the fire, said John Buono, a fire investigator for 
the Metro Arson Strike Team 
</P>
<P>
The video shows the boys, both wearing dark shorts and shirts and carrying 
butterfly nets, standing only a few feet away from the fire in its first 
stages, Buono said. 
</P>
<P>
The 25-acre brush fire, which spread from a canyon, was in the 5700 block of 
Rancho Hills Drive. 
</P>
<P>
Anyone with information about the two boys is asked to call Crime Stoppers at 
235-TIPS. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA082690-0160 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 267374 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
August 26, 1990, Sunday, South Bay Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Metro; Part B; Page 6; Column 1 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
121 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
BICYCLIST KILLED IN INGLEWOOD BY HIT-RUN DRIVER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Inglewood police have asked for the public's help in finding the driver of a 
Honda car who fled the scene after striking and killing a bicyclist early 
Saturday morning. 
</P>
<P>
The bicyclist, 31-year-old Rogelio Sanchez of Inglewood, apparently died 
instantly when he was struck in the 3800 block of West Imperial Highway about 
12:30 a.m., Sgt. Alex Perez said. 
</P>
<P>
Investigators have found no witnesses to the accident, but said they found 
evidence indicating Sanchez was hit by a Honda automobile. The model and color 
of the car have not been determined, Perez said. 
</P>
<P>
Anyone with information about the car or its driver is asked to call Inglewood 
police traffic investigator John Winters or Officer James Stuart at 412-5207. 
</P>
</TEXT>
