<P>
One cannot be a professional until he or she has been recognized by the 
profession. I would suggest that the only rationalization for eschewing a 
license stems from fear and insecurity rather than from a holier-than-thou 
arrogance. 
</P>
<P>
Stick to picking paint and wallpaper, Mr. Schweitzer, or see if you can pass 
the test. 
</P>
<P>
JAMES LECRON 
