<HEADLINE>
<P>
CUT BY THE 'KNIFE' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
On July 30 I had the choice of watching various programs, including "American 
Masters." 
</P>
<P>
Knowing that KCET probably would repeat that program, I opted for ABC's "The 
Knife and Gun Club," starring Perry King and Dorian Harewood, and was 
pleasantly surprised. 
</P>
<P>
The show was gripping and factual and I thoroughly enjoyed it. I just hope that 
it was not an unsold pilot and will never be seen again. 
</P>
<P>
Donna L. Starr, Tustin 
</P>
<P>
Sorry to be the bearer of bad tidings, but "The Knife and Gun Club" indeed was 
an unsold pilot and, in all likelihood, will never be seen again. 
</P>
